Security Information
Knowledge is a powerful defense against fraud and scams - we’re here to help you stay informed.
Learn more
about how Merrill protects your personal information, and discover additional security resources to explore by visiting our
Security Center
.
Visit Merrill’s
Security Center
today for tips and tools on how to increase your security and help stay protected against fraud and scams.
Remember:
Do not provide access codes, personal and financial information via email, text or to unsolicited callers. We will never call you to ask you for this information
Report Fraud:
If you suspect you’re a victim of fraud, contact us immediately at 1.800.MERRILL (637.7455) or speak to your financial advisor.
If you receive a suspicious call, text or email from someone claiming to be from Merrill or Bank of America, do not respond and do not click links or open/download attachments. Instead, send it to
abuse@bankofamerica.com
and delete it.
Forward Suspicious Email to Us
